messages.messageBody:
I have been reading all the "math" posts, mainly because I am a
nib :) don't want to miss anythng, (on this list anyway :)). I am
LOUSY at math :) BUT! I have this book :) The World Treasury of
Physics, Astronomy, and Mathematics. I bought a Looooooong time ago,
thinking that I would read it, (like I have the time ), and I might
benefit from it..... I am much older and I have realized that I will
not read it, especially since my interest has wandered else where
with my kidlets and all :) So, back to my original thought ;) This
book I have, I have no need for, and if anyone is interested in it I
am willing to send it free of charge......I just dont need it and
although I LOVE books, it isnt something I will read. Any of you math
people :) are welcome to it! Just let me know!
Indiana Tami
